Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C and take the @duck breasts{2} out of the fridge so
it can come to room temperature. Finely chop the @red chilli{1/2}. Peel the
@carrot{1}, remove the top and bottom and chop into roughly ½cm cubes. Peel,
quarter and core the @apple{1}, then chop into 1cm cubes. Halve, peel and
finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}. Chop the leaves of the @spring greens{75%g}
into roughly 1cm slices (discard the core). Finely chop the
@flat leaf parsley{5}(chopped, stalks and all).

Put a splash of @oil{} in a #small saucepan{} on medium-low heat. Add the
apple, a sprinkle of @?sugar{} (if you have some) and a splash of @water{}.
Pop a #lid{} on the pan and cook until the apple has softened, ~{10-15%minutes}.
Remove the lid for the last few mins of cooking time so the apple can thicken.
Take the pan off the heat and set aside with the lid on to keep warm.

> Use a knob of butter instead if you have some.

Season the duck breast with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Make three diagonal
cuts into the skin with a sharp #knife{}. Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high
heat (no oil) and lay in the duck, skin-side down. Cook until the skin is
golden, ~{7%minutes}. Transfer to a lined #baking tray{}, skin-side up. (Keep
the pan!). Roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{7%minutes}.

> We like our duck pink, if you like it well done give it 15 mins in the oven.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another frying pan on medium heat. Add the chilli,
carrot and shallot. Cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. Drain and thoroughly rinse
the @green lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Once the veggies are soft, add in the
lentils and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1/2}(tsp) and @water{}.
Cook for ~{3%minutes}, then take the pan off the heat and set aside until it's
time to serve.

Once the duck is cooked, remove from your oven and leave to rest for a few
minutes. Pour out all but a drizzle of oil from the pan you used to fry it and
pop on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the spring greens. Season with a pinch
of salt and a good grind of pepper. Fry until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reheat your lentils, stir through the parsley and divide between plates. Serve
the spring greens on the side. Carve the duck into slices and arrange on top of
the lentils with a generous spoonful of caramelised apple. Enjoy!